<section xml:id="reusing-classes_vocabulary">
<title>Vocabulary</title>
<ul>
<li>
<title>refactor:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>refactor</h></idx>
To restructure or reorganize existing source code without changing its behavior.</p></li>
<li>
<title>abstract class:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>abstract class</h></idx>
A class that is declared as <c>abstract</c>; it cannot be instantiated, and it may (or may not) include abstract methods.</p></li>
<li>
<title>concrete class:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>concrete class</h></idx>
A class that is <em>not</em> declared as <c>abstract</c>; each of its methods must have an implementation.</p></li>
</ul>
</section>
